[normal]Third: advocacy of violent liberation struggle rather than peace with the adversary
[normal]A delegitimized and demonized adversary is not a real partner for peace. Accordingly, no peaceful solution to the conflict is advocated in the PA books used in UN
[normal]RWA's schools. Instead, a violent struggle of liberation against its occupation (both before and after 1967) is promoted. This struggle, which is never said to be restricted to the areas of the 
[normal]West Bank
[normal] and the Gaza Strip
[normal] alone
[normal], is made more compelling by
[normal] the use of the traditional Islamic concepts of 
[normal]Jihad
[normal] and martyrdom [
[normal]Shahadah
[normal]] within its framework. Examples:
